Error: Load from word-typed value requires @a16.
   ╭─[ tests/golden/fixtures/syntax-mode-typed-width-errors-load-word/input.k65:7:5 ]
   │
 7 │     lda regs.ctrl
   │     ──────┬──────  
   │           ╰──────── load under @a8
   │ 
   │ Help: the load target is var `regs.ctrl`; switch the a register to @a16 before the load (active mode is @a8), or change the source's declared width if it actually holds a @a8 value
   │ 
   │ Note: K816 enforces operand-width matching at lowering time: typed loads/stores must run under a register-width mode (`@a8`/`@a16` or `@i8`/`@i16`) that produces opcodes of the correct width. The 65816 has no "narrowing" load that drops half a 16-bit value into an 8-bit register — the encoding itself differs.
───╯
